    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** as our definitive anchor, boasting an elite 81.88 efficiency score. Facing Shota Imanaga (Burke), **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 14% platoon adjustment and a favorable leadoff spot, making him our primary source for run production and high-ceiling offensive output. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.99) round out our top-tier plays; **Jackson Merrill** is particularly intriguing due to a rare 2% boost tied to a slow-delivering pitcher, which increases his probability of swiping a bag\u2014a critical metric given our aggressive focus on the scarcest category of stolen bases.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved keeping **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** on the bench, despite his impressive 48.73 efficiency. While his raw metrics remain elite, the matchup against Shohei Ohtani (Ohtani) creates a severe drag on his SP Skill factor (-19%), effectively suppressing his scoring potential below that of **Liam Hicks** and **Jacob Wilson**. We are playing the numbers, and the optimizer prefers the platoon advantages presented by **Nasim Nunez** and **Josh Lowe** over forcing **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** into a low-probability matchup.\n\nWarning flags persist regarding the high-end opposing talent we face today. While **Kyle Tucker** (64.17) holds a strong score, the face-off against Dylan Cease requires vigilance; any deviation in his xwOBA or a slight decline in velocity during the early innings could dampen his floor. Additionally, we are monitoring the bottom of the order with **Andy Pages** and **Luis Robert Jr.**; their sub-50 scores are heavily impacted by negative park factors and poor platoon splits, respectively. We will keep a close watch on these margins as the day progresses to ensure we are preserving our game caps without sacrificing our competitive edge in the 5x5.",
